.\" auto-reboot(1) - Schedule conditional system reboots via systemd timers
.TH AUTO\-REBOOT 1 "2026-03-12" "1.2.0" "System Administration"
.
.SH NAME
auto\-reboot \- schedule conditional system reboots via systemd timers
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B auto\-reboot
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B auto\-reboot
schedules system reboots via systemd transient timers based on configurable
conditions. It checks whether the system requires a reboot due to pending
updates or excessive uptime, then schedules a reboot at the specified time
using
.BR systemd\-run (1).
.PP
Dry\-run is the default mode. Use
.B \-N
to execute for real.
.PP
Reboot conditions (any triggers scheduling):
.IP \(bu 2
System updates require reboot
.RI ( /var/run/reboot\-required " exists)"
.IP \(bu 2
Uptime exceeds maximum threshold (default: 14 days)
.IP \(bu 2
Manual force reboot via
.B \-f
.PP
The script automatically elevates to root via
.BR sudo (8)
if the invoking user is in the sudo group.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Execution Mode"
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Test mode, no execution. This is the default.
.TP
.BR \-N ", " \-\-not\-dry\-run
Execute for real.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force\-reboot
Force reboot regardless of conditions. Bypasses reboot\-required and uptime
checks; time and day restrictions still apply.
.
.SS "Output Control"
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Verbose output. This is the default.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress informational messages. Error messages are always shown.
Recommended for cron usage.
.
.SS "Scheduling"
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-max\-uptime\-days " \fIDAYS\fR"
Maximum uptime in days before a reboot is triggered.
Must be a positive integer. Default: 14.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-reboot\-time " \fIHH:MM\fR"
Time to schedule the reboot in 24\-hour format.
Valid range: 00:00 to 23:59. Default: 22:00.
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-allowed\-days " \fIDAYS\fR"
Restrict reboots to specific days of the week. Accepts a comma\-separated
list of day names or numbers. See
.B DAY SPECIFICATIONS
below. When omitted, any day is allowed.
.
.SS "Schedule Management"
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
List all active auto\-reboot timers.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-delete " \fITIMER\fR"
Delete a specific auto\-reboot timer.
.I TIMER
can be the full name
.RI ( auto\-reboot\-1234.timer ),
partial name
.RI ( auto\-reboot\-1234 ),
or just the numeric ID
.RI ( 1234 ).
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-delete\-all
Delete all auto\-reboot timers. Prompts for confirmation when used with
.BR \-N .
.
.SS "Other"
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-install
Install auto\-reboot to
.I /usr/local/bin
and install the
.B systemd\-container
package if needed.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help text and exit.
.PP
Short options can be bundled:
.B \-Nqf
is equivalent to
.BR "\-N \-q \-f" .
.
.SH DAY SPECIFICATIONS
The
.B \-\-allowed\-days
option accepts comma\-separated values in any of these formats:
.PP
.TS
l l.
Short names	Sun, Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Fri, Sat
Full names	Sunday, Monday, \&..., Saturday
Numbers	0 (Sunday) through 6 (Saturday)
Mixed	Mon,Wed,5
.TE
.PP
Case insensitive. Whitespace around commas is ignored.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MACHINE_REBOOT_TIME
Default reboot time in HH:MM format. Default: 22:00.
Overridden by
.BR \-\-reboot\-time .
.TP
.B MACHINE_UPTIME_MAXDAYS
Default maximum uptime in days. Default: 14.
Overridden by
.BR \-\-max\-uptime\-days .
.
.SH SCHEDULING LOGIC
.IP 1. 3
.B No day restrictions:
Schedules for today at the specified time, or tomorrow if that time has
already passed.
.IP 2. 3
.B With day restrictions:
Scans up to 7 days ahead for the next allowed day at the specified time.
.IP 3. 3
.B Force reboot:
Bypasses reboot\-required and uptime checks. Time and day restrictions
still apply.
.PP
Timers are created as systemd transient units named
.IR auto\-reboot\-EPOCH .timer
using
.BR systemd\-run (1)
with
.BR AccuracySec=1s .
.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
General error (systemd not running, scheduling failed, root required).
.TP
.B 22
Invalid argument (bad time format, invalid day, missing option value).
.
.SH EXAMPLES
Check if reboot is needed (dry run):
.PP
.RS
.nf
auto\-reboot
.fi
.RE
.PP
Schedule reboot if conditions are met:
.PP
.RS
.nf
auto\-reboot \-N
.fi
.RE
.PP
Force reboot at 3 AM, quietly:
.PP
.RS
.nf
auto\-reboot \-Nqf \-r 03:00
.fi
.RE
.PP
Restrict to weekends only:
.PP
.RS
.nf
auto\-reboot \-a Sat,Sun \-r 04:00 \-N
.fi
.RE
.PP
List and delete scheduled reboots:
.PP
.RS
.nf
auto\-reboot \-\-list
auto\-reboot \-\-delete 1753063354
auto\-reboot \-ND
.fi
.RE
.
.SS "Cron Integration"
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Daily check, reboot Sunday at 4 AM if uptime > 14 days
0 23 * * * /usr/local/bin/auto\-reboot \-q \-m 14 \-r 04:00 \-a Sun \-N

# Check every 6 hours, reboot if uptime > 30 days
0 */6 * * * /usr/local/bin/auto\-reboot \-q \-m 30 \-N

# Weekly forced reboot Sunday at 3 AM
0 2 * * 0 /usr/local/bin/auto\-reboot \-qf \-r 03:00 \-N
.fi
.RE
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/run/reboot\-required
Presence triggers a reboot. Created by package managers when kernel or
library updates require a restart.
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/auto\-reboot
Default installation location (via
.BR \-\-install ).
.
.SH LOGGING
All schedule and delete operations are logged to syslog via
.BR logger (1)
with tag
.BR auto\-reboot .
View logs with:
.PP
.RS
.nf
journalctl \-t auto\-reboot
.fi
.RE
.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.BR systemd\-run (1)
From the
.B systemd\-container
package. Install with
.B auto\-reboot \-\-install
or
.BR "apt install systemd\-container" .
.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR systemd\-run (1),
.BR systemctl (1),
.BR shutdown (8),
.BR sudo (8),
.BR logger (1)
.
